<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-03-23T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-03-23T19:00:00-05:00" n="627" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d627">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">411.6131/3–1350: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Embassy in the Soviet Union</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-03-23T19:00:00-05:00">March 23,
                                    1950—7 p. m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>243. Urtels 805 Mar 10, 829 Mar 13.<note n="1" xml:id="d627fn1">Latter
                                telegram not printed.</note> Abrogation US–USSR commercial agreement
                            on ground Sov establishment unrealistic exchange rate renders agreement
                            obsolete, making impossible normal traditional commercial exchanges,
                            considered inadvisable because ruble not internatl currency nor element
                            US-Sov trade. <gloss target="#t_Embdes1">Embdes</gloss> 233 Mar 3 being
                            carefully considered and Dept believes more appropriate opportunity
                            action this connection may arise.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>